Please, make the water go down.

615
00:34:36.200 --> 00:34:39.670
[Dramatic instrumental music]

616
00:34:49.240 --> 00:34:50.673
Oh, my God!

617
00:34:53.080 --> 00:34:54.877
POLLY: This was fun.
REUBEN: Yes.

618
00:34:56.120 --> 00:34:58.634
If I'd known your grandmother
embroidered that towel...

619
00:34:58.720 --> 00:35:01.234
-I would've never--
-Really, that's okay.

620
00:35:01.840 --> 00:35:05.594
-Okay, well, good night, Polly.
-Good night, Reuben.

621
00:35:06.240 --> 00:35:07.639
-Good night.
-Okay.

622
00:35:07.720 --> 00:35:09.870
REUBEN: All right, okay.
POLLY: All right, that's nice.

623
00:35:16.160 --> 00:35:18.628
SANDY: Why would you make
number two in her apartment?

624
00:35:18.720 --> 00:35:21.314
She asked me to come upstairs.
What should I have done?

625
00:35:21.400 --> 00:35:23.960
Tell her you're tired
and shag ass out of there.

626
00:35:24.040 --> 00:35:25.029
Guys.

627
00:35:25.880 --> 00:35:27.950
SANDY: What?
REUBEN: I called her to apologise.

628
00:35:28.040 --> 00:35:31.589
It doesn't matter, because I doubt
she'll ever want to see me again.

629
00:35:31.680 --> 00:35:33.716
REUBEN: I got to call you back.
SANDY: Cool.

630
00:35:33.800 --> 00:35:34.869
REUBEN: Mr. Van Lew?

631
00:35:36.080 --> 00:35:38.514
LELAND: Feffer?
REUBEN: Yes. Hi, Reuben Feffer.

632
00:35:38.600 --> 00:35:40.477
I recognised you
from the Forbes cover.

633
00:35:40.560 --> 00:35:43.358
You're way early, sport.
Come on, then. Get in.

634
00:35:43.440 --> 00:35:45.635
REUBEN: This the service elevator?
LELAND: Yeah.

635
00:35:46.080 --> 00:35:49.038
I don't think we'll have a problem
with this insurance business.

636
00:35:49.120 --> 00:35:52.112
Sure, I take chances, but you can't
build a successful business...

637
00:35:52.200 --> 00:35:53.952
-without the occasional risk.
-Of course.

638
00:35:54.040 --> 00:35:57.396
What I'm trying to determine are the
kinds of risks you actually take.

639
00:35:57.480 --> 00:35:58.799
Only the calculated ones.

640
00:35:58.880 --> 00:36:00.871
Trust me, I plan on being around
for ages.

641
00:36:01.160 --> 00:36:04.357
REUBEN: We'd really love to give you
a policy if we can make it work.

642
00:36:04.440 --> 00:36:06.590
-We'll make it work, sport.
-Great.

643
00:36:07.240 --> 00:36:10.550
-So, what are we doing on the roof?
-I'm doing a bit of a BASE jump.

644
00:36:10.640 --> 00:36:13.632
Here, keep the walkie on channel 13,
all right?

645
00:36:13.720 --> 00:36:15.438
I don't know
what you're talking about.

646
00:36:15.520 --> 00:36:17.431
LELAND: A free-fall
from an inanimate object.

647
00:36:17.520 --> 00:36:20.273
Always carry me chute in case
I find a good launching point.

648
00:36:20.360 --> 00:36:21.349
Oh, no.

649
00:36:21.440 --> 00:36:22.429
[Phone rings]

650
00:36:22.520 --> 00:36:23.839
Don't do anything, all right?

651
00:36:23.920 --> 00:36:27.879
POLLY: Hey, Reuben, it's Polly.
REUBEN: Polly, how's it going?

652
00:36:27.960 --> 00:36:31.111
-I'll shout when I'm through, okay?
-No, that's not all right.

653
00:36:31.200 --> 00:36:32.235
Can I call you back?

654
00:36:32.320 --> 00:36:34.788
POLLY: I just wanted to tell you
I got your message.

655
00:36:34.880 --> 00:36:37.838
Let's just start over
and forget about the loofah thing.

656
00:36:37.920 --> 00:36:39.194
Holy shit! No!

657
00:36:39.280 --> 00:36:40.269
[Leland whooping]

658
00:36:40.880 --> 00:36:41.869
Holy shit!

659
00:36:41.960 --> 00:36:43.518
POLLY: I didn't even like that loofah.

660
00:36:44.080 --> 00:36:47.311
Relax. Leland's meeting
with the insurance guy right now.

661
00:36:47.400 --> 00:36:49.072
LELAND: Whoa! Yeah!

662
00:36:53.120 --> 00:36:54.394
Oh, crap!

663
00:36:54.520 --> 00:36:56.988
REUBEN: Oh, shit!
POLLY: I'll call you in a few days.

664
00:36:57.080 --> 00:36:59.514
LELAND: [On radio] Leland to Feffer.
You there, mate?

665
00:36:59.960 --> 00:37:01.951
Yes, Feffer to Leland, hello?

666
00:37:02.040 --> 00:37:05.476
LELAND: [On radio] Come and give us
a hand. Think I fractured me coccyx.

667
00:37:07.560 --> 00:37:09.676
[Soothing lndian music]

668
00:37:12.000 --> 00:37:14.912
POLLY: Look at that.
You got me a new loofah.

669
00:37:15.000 --> 00:37:16.149
It's from Finland...

670
00:37:16.240 --> 00:37:19.038
and the salesman said
it has a very ergonomic design.

671
00:37:19.120 --> 00:37:22.908
Oh, Reuben, that's really....
Thank you, that's really sweet.

672
00:37:23.080 --> 00:37:24.479
Oh, my God!

673
00:37:25.000 --> 00:37:26.752
I don't believe this!

674
00:37:26.840 --> 00:37:28.558
What are you doing here?

675
00:37:28.640 --> 00:37:30.198
We're having an early supper.

676
00:37:30.280 --> 00:37:32.032
I wanted your father
to try new cuisines.

677
00:37:32.120 --> 00:37:33.155
It's only 3:00.

678
00:37:33.240 --> 00:37:35.037
It's a crime to beat
the dinner crowds?

679
00:37:35.120 --> 00:37:38.271
VlVlAN: Who is this young woman....
REUBEN: This is Polly Prince.

680
00:37:38.360 --> 00:37:41.477
Polly, these are my parents,
Irving and Vivian Feffer.

681
00:37:41.560 --> 00:37:44.199
-It's so good meeting you.
-How are you?

682
00:37:44.280 --> 00:37:47.033
I can't believe you're
eating lndian. You hate spicy food.

683
00:37:47.120 --> 00:37:48.519
REUBEN: No, I don't.

684
00:37:49.400 --> 00:37:52.039
Well, I'm going to....
I'm going to ask....

685
00:37:52.240 --> 00:37:54.515
I'm going to ask
this nice Native American man...

686
00:37:54.600 --> 00:37:55.669
to get us a bigger table.

687
00:37:55.760 --> 00:37:58.035
They're lndian.
You can call them lndian. It's okay.

688
00:37:58.120 --> 00:38:02.716
VlVlAN: Hi. Need big table, please.
Four people. Many thanks.

689
00:38:05.360 --> 00:38:06.475
Okay.

690
00:38:07.360 --> 00:38:09.510
VlVlAN: Now, how do you kids
know each other?

691
00:38:09.600 --> 00:38:13.354
We went to middle school together.
We were both in the Model UN.

692
00:38:13.440 --> 00:38:15.829
You still work in government, honey?

693
00:38:15.920 --> 00:38:18.480
No. I'm a waitress.

694
00:38:19.880 --> 00:38:21.677
She's also writing
a children's book.

695
00:38:21.760 --> 00:38:23.398
Oh, very nice.

696
00:38:24.120 --> 00:38:26.350
You'll never guess
who I ran into yesterday.

697
00:38:26.440 --> 00:38:27.998
REUBEN: Who?
VlVlAN: Lisa's mother.

698
00:38:28.080 --> 00:38:29.115
REUBEN: That's good.

699
00:38:29.200 --> 00:38:31.430
Dad, did you try this....
What's this called?

700
00:38:31.520 --> 00:38:33.397
-Saag.
-Saag. Did you try this?

701
00:38:33.480 --> 00:38:37.029
Apparently, Lisa's doing wonderfully
down there in St. Barts...

702
00:38:37.120 --> 00:38:38.553
selling villas, happy.

703
00:38:38.640 --> 00:38:39.993
That's good for her.

704
00:38:40.080 --> 00:38:42.548
POLLY: Now, who's Lisa?
REUBEN: Not important.

705
00:38:42.640 --> 00:38:44.198
Lisa is Reuben's wife.

706
00:38:45.240 --> 00:38:47.959
She left him for another man
on their honeymoon.

707
00:38:48.320 --> 00:38:51.551
Are we ready for the cheque?
I think we'll take the cheque.

708
00:38:51.680 --> 00:38:52.795
What?

709
00:38:53.680 --> 00:38:57.639
-Well, your dad seems really nice.
-Yes, a man of few words.

710
00:38:58.480 --> 00:39:02.268
I just want you to know, I was going
to tell you about Lisa. I just....

711
00:39:02.360 --> 00:39:04.396
I was embarrassed and l....

712
00:39:04.640 --> 00:39:06.915
I guess because I hadn't seen you
for so long--

713
00:39:07.000 --> 00:39:08.911
It's so okay. I understand.

714
00:39:09.000 --> 00:39:11.992
I was an idiot. I should've told you
the truth from the start.

715
00:39:12.080 --> 00:39:13.911
Really, I'm not upset.

716
00:39:15.360 --> 00:39:18.113
-But when did this happen?
-Two weeks ago.

717
00:39:18.680 --> 00:39:20.830
Two weeks ago?

718
00:39:21.880 --> 00:39:24.474
Oh, my God! Are you okay?

719
00:39:26.720 --> 00:39:28.676
Well, it was a pretty big shock.

720
00:39:30.120 --> 00:39:33.999
I walked in on her, on Lisa with...

721
00:39:34.480 --> 00:39:37.836
a scuba instructor on the first day
