00:54:12.320 --> 00:54:15.232
17 people eat these nuts
on a given night. Okay?

959
00:54:15.320 --> 00:54:18.073
If they've been here for two weeks,
we're talking about...

960
00:54:18.160 --> 00:54:21.197
238 people who've dipped their
dirty hands into that bowl.

961
00:54:21.280 --> 00:54:23.111
Dirty. Why are their hands dirty?

962
00:54:23.200 --> 00:54:24.838
Only one out of six people...

963
00:54:24.920 --> 00:54:26.672
wash hands
when they go to the bathroom.

964
00:54:26.760 --> 00:54:29.228
When you think you're innocently
eating a bar snack...

965
00:54:29.320 --> 00:54:31.356
you're ingesting
potentially deadly bacteria...

966
00:54:31.440 --> 00:54:33.431
from 39 soil-handed strangers.

967
00:54:33.520 --> 00:54:35.636
People wonder why
they get E. coli poisoning...

968
00:54:35.720 --> 00:54:36.994
or salmonella or hepatitis.

969
00:54:37.080 --> 00:54:40.436
They should look at the snack bowl
at their local watering hole.

970
00:54:41.760 --> 00:54:45.070
I'm not being neurotic.
It's a hot zone in there.

971
00:54:49.520 --> 00:54:51.511
How could you have eaten those?

972
00:54:51.600 --> 00:54:54.114
I made such a compelling argument.

973
00:54:54.200 --> 00:54:56.430
I like to live life on the edge.

974
00:54:57.000 --> 00:54:59.434
POLLY: Thank you.
REUBEN: Yeah, you never know.

975
00:55:07.000 --> 00:55:10.470
[Upbeat salsa music]

976
00:55:11.280 --> 00:55:12.952
You don't have to do this.

977
00:55:13.040 --> 00:55:15.793
I don't care that you don't know
how to dance!

978
00:55:15.880 --> 00:55:18.348
I thought I'd give it one last try.
Hey, Javi.

979
00:55:18.440 --> 00:55:20.351
Hey, Reuben. You ready?

980
00:55:21.600 --> 00:55:22.669
POLLY: What's happening?

981
00:55:22.760 --> 00:55:24.478
HECTOR:!Fuerte!
POLLY: What?

982
00:55:27.120 --> 00:55:28.553
What are you doing?

983
00:56:04.160 --> 00:56:05.752
[Reuben crashing into stage]

984
00:56:14.640 --> 00:56:16.631
[Yipping and shouting]

985
00:56:46.120 --> 00:56:48.509
I don't know where that came from!

986
00:56:48.600 --> 00:56:50.192
POLLY: It was just awesome.

987
00:56:51.200 --> 00:56:52.155
Holy shit.

988
00:56:59.720 --> 00:57:01.676
What are you doing here?

989
00:57:04.560 --> 00:57:05.834
I'm back.

990
00:57:08.360 --> 00:57:09.713
Who's this?

991
00:57:10.400 --> 00:57:12.755
REUBEN: This is my girlfriend.
POLLY: What?

992
00:57:12.840 --> 00:57:14.990
-You have a girlfriend?
-I'm not your girlfriend.

993
00:57:15.080 --> 00:57:18.231
I mean, we're just, kind of....
Hi, I'm Polly.

994
00:57:20.000 --> 00:57:21.752
LlSA: Lisa.
POLLY: Right.

995
00:57:29.240 --> 00:57:33.438
You guys probably have a lot
to talk about, so I'll just go.

996
00:57:33.520 --> 00:57:36.239
REUBEN: I don't want you to go.
POLLY: I want to. Bye, Lisa.

997
00:57:36.320 --> 00:57:38.197
POLLY: Nice to meet you.
REUBEN: Don't go.

998
00:57:38.280 --> 00:57:40.271
You got to talk about it.

999
00:57:41.040 --> 00:57:42.553
I'm just going to go.

1000
00:57:49.120 --> 00:57:50.155
REUBEN: I don't understand.

1001
00:57:50.240 --> 00:57:52.913
I thought you were really happy
with Claude.

1002
00:57:53.000 --> 00:57:56.788
I was, for a few weeks, but all he
talked about was scuba diving.

1003
00:57:56.880 --> 00:57:59.155
-Really?
-I missed you, Reuben.

1004
00:57:59.240 --> 00:58:02.437
I missed you, too, but come on!
What was I supposed to do?

1005
00:58:02.520 --> 00:58:04.715
I moved on. I'm in a relationship.

1006
00:58:04.800 --> 00:58:06.313
-What, with that Polly person?
-Yeah.

1007
00:58:06.400 --> 00:58:08.231
She doesn't call herself
your girlfriend.

1008
00:58:08.320 --> 00:58:10.959
That's.... No, she just doesn't like
the phrasing.

1009
00:58:11.040 --> 00:58:13.508
LlSA: Okay, then,
let me just ask you this.

1010
00:58:13.600 --> 00:58:17.434
Are you really going to spend
the rest of your life with her?

1011
00:58:17.920 --> 00:58:19.433
I don't know, Lisa.

1012
00:58:19.760 --> 00:58:22.354
Because I'm ready to do that
with you.

1013
00:58:22.480 --> 00:58:25.119
I made a mistake,
and I took you for granted.

1014
00:58:25.280 --> 00:58:29.114
But I promise you that I will
never, ever hurt you again.

1015
00:58:31.480 --> 00:58:33.391
I love you, Reuben.

1016
00:58:40.080 --> 00:58:41.593
REUBEN: You know what?

1017
00:58:42.240 --> 00:58:45.630
I think you should
go stay with your parents. Okay?

1018
00:58:45.720 --> 00:58:48.393
REUBEN: I've to leave in a week.
LlSA: Where are you going?

1019
00:58:48.480 --> 00:58:51.552
I'm going into the house
I bought for us. Remember?

1020
00:58:51.640 --> 00:58:54.473
Let's do it together.
Let's go move into our house.

1021
00:58:54.560 --> 00:58:57.950
We don't just....
No. We can't just go.... I can't....

1022
00:59:01.240 --> 00:59:04.198
I don't even know
what to say right now, okay? So....

1023
00:59:07.400 --> 00:59:08.515
Okay.

1024
00:59:11.880 --> 00:59:13.871
POLLY: If you want to get
back together--

1025
00:59:13.960 --> 00:59:16.793
No, I wouldn't be seeing you
if I was planning--

1026
00:59:16.880 --> 00:59:19.952
POLLY: It's cool. You guys are
married. She came back.

1027
00:59:20.600 --> 00:59:22.795
How's it coming
with Herb Lazare, D.D.S.?

1028
00:59:23.200 --> 00:59:25.873
I haven't even gotten to it.
I'm still working on Van Lew.

1029
00:59:25.960 --> 00:59:28.474
I thought you decided on Van Lew
two weeks ago.

1030
00:59:28.560 --> 00:59:30.710
We present to AFLAC on Wednesday.

1031
00:59:30.800 --> 00:59:33.155
REUBEN: Can you hang on? Hang on.
POLLY: I have to go.

1032
00:59:33.240 --> 00:59:35.913
STAN: Better not be bonus-hunting on me.
REUBEN: Bonus-hunting?

1033
00:59:36.000 --> 00:59:39.276
That man's career's on the line.
I owe him a thorough analysis.

1034
00:59:39.360 --> 00:59:40.429
All right.

1035
00:59:40.640 --> 00:59:43.074
I'm going to Barbados with
my mistress for the weekend.

1036
00:59:43.160 --> 00:59:45.754
I want this Van Lew thing settled
by the time I get back.

1037
00:59:45.840 --> 00:59:47.990
I am on it, and I'll make it happen.

1038
00:59:48.120 --> 00:59:49.519
Good things.

1039
00:59:49.600 --> 00:59:50.589
[Dial tone]

1040
00:59:51.360 --> 00:59:52.395
Damn!

1041
00:59:53.760 --> 00:59:55.113
LARRY: Hey, pal.
REUBEN: Hey, Larry.

1042
00:59:55.200 --> 00:59:57.111
Lisa dropped this off for you.

1043
00:59:59.760 --> 01:00:00.829
Thanks.

1044
01:00:08.000 --> 01:00:10.992
[Sentimental instrumental music]

1045
01:00:12.840 --> 01:00:16.071
REUBEN: I met Lisa, who showed
me an apartment, which I rented...

1046
01:00:16.160 --> 01:00:18.754
REUBEN: so she'd go out with me.
LlSA: Gave him a good price.

1047
01:00:18.840 --> 01:00:20.831
REUBEN: Not good enough. She's a killer.

1048
01:00:28.200 --> 01:00:31.670
