-Polly?
-Yeah.

1065
01:01:18.360 --> 01:01:21.318
No way. Just cut your losses
and get back with Lisa.

1066
01:01:21.400 --> 01:01:24.437
I checked it three times.
It says she's the safer choice.

1067
01:01:24.520 --> 01:01:25.794
Whatever.

1068
01:01:27.240 --> 01:01:30.516
By the way, is your health okay?
You're looking thin.

1069
01:01:30.600 --> 01:01:32.716
Polly's been making me
eat ethnic food...

1070
01:01:32.800 --> 01:01:35.109
so I've been throwing up
a lot lately.

1071
01:01:35.560 --> 01:01:36.629
Cool.

1072
01:01:36.720 --> 01:01:37.994
Polly Prince.

1073
01:01:39.840 --> 01:01:41.319
Polly Feffer.

1074
01:01:43.720 --> 01:01:45.551
Polly Prince-Feffer.

1075
01:01:45.960 --> 01:01:48.520
You can't cancel.
You were so excited to go.

1076
01:01:48.680 --> 01:01:49.829
I know, but--

1077
01:01:49.920 --> 01:01:53.037
HOSTESS: We fell in love
with these funny Bolivian mud huts.

1078
01:01:53.120 --> 01:01:54.758
POLLY: Hold on.
HOSTESS: So our designer...

1079
01:01:54.840 --> 01:01:56.910
used a similar colour palette
in here.

1080
01:01:57.000 --> 01:02:00.675
Hi. I'm sorry, I'm on the phone.
Would you just please keep it....

1081
01:02:02.280 --> 01:02:05.431
Also, I feel weird going away
for the weekend...

1082
01:02:05.520 --> 01:02:08.796
POLLY: when your wife just came back.
REUBEN: You're making this a big deal.

1083
01:02:08.880 --> 01:02:11.678
REUBEN: I told you, I'm not getting back
together with her.

1084
01:02:13.000 --> 01:02:14.433
REUBEN: You're coming?
POLLY: I'm coming.

1085
01:02:14.920 --> 01:02:16.433
REUBEN: All right.
POLLY: Okay?

1086
01:02:16.800 --> 01:02:17.789
REUBEN: Bye.
POLLY: Bye.

1087
01:02:19.880 --> 01:02:23.350
[Upbeat pop music]

1088
01:02:41.680 --> 01:02:45.070
LELAND: Good. You're a natural.
POLLY: This is amazing!

1089
01:02:45.320 --> 01:02:48.278
Hey, Leland, are those storm clouds
up ahead?

1090
01:02:49.840 --> 01:02:53.719
No, we might get a light dusting.
Nothing to write home about.

1091
01:02:57.840 --> 01:02:59.193
Are you sure you're all right?

1092
01:02:59.280 --> 01:03:02.113
REUBEN: I'm okay. I don't think
I have my sea legs yet.

1093
01:03:02.200 --> 01:03:04.270
REUBEN: I'll be out in a sec.
POLLY: All right.

1094
01:03:04.880 --> 01:03:06.108
POLLY: Oh, God.

1095
01:03:07.200 --> 01:03:09.668
[Riskmaster program opens]

1096
01:03:11.600 --> 01:03:14.831
I know we haven't been seeing each
other long, but I feel like...

1097
01:03:14.920 --> 01:03:17.195
it's time we take things
to the next level...

1098
01:03:17.280 --> 01:03:20.556
and I'd like you
to consider moving in with me.

1099
01:03:28.960 --> 01:03:30.996
Why don't we just move in together?

1100
01:03:38.680 --> 01:03:41.399
Oh, yeah, we're going to have
ourselves a tussle.

1101
01:03:42.000 --> 01:03:43.991
[Ferret squeaks]

1102
01:03:44.080 --> 01:03:47.834
Rodolfo's in your toiletry kit.
Did you know that?

1103
01:03:48.120 --> 01:03:50.156
Did you pack him, or did you....

1104
01:03:50.240 --> 01:03:51.514
What is this?

1105
01:03:51.600 --> 01:03:54.876
Why am I in your computer
on your Riskmaster thingy?

1106
01:03:54.960 --> 01:03:56.871
Okay, you know what?
I can explain this.

1107
01:03:56.960 --> 01:03:59.599
It's fascinating, actually.
I learned a lot about myself.

1108
01:03:59.680 --> 01:04:03.389
I've learned that I have no career,
I'm flaky, I like ethnic food.

1109
01:04:03.480 --> 01:04:05.072
Would you let me explain?

1110
01:04:05.160 --> 01:04:08.311
Lisa came back, and I've been trying
to figure things out.

1111
01:04:08.400 --> 01:04:12.154
-What are you figuring out?
-Just about us, and our future.

1112
01:04:12.680 --> 01:04:15.592
Future? What are you talking about?
What future?

1113
01:04:15.680 --> 01:04:18.478
Reuben, come on.
This is a fling, you know?

1114
01:04:18.560 --> 01:04:20.915
What, did you think
we'd get married?

1115
01:04:21.000 --> 01:04:22.399
REUBEN: Whoa! Maybe.

1116
01:04:23.240 --> 01:04:25.196
I was gonna ask you
to move in with me first.

1117
01:04:25.280 --> 01:04:28.670
POLLY: You expect me to move
to the suburbs? Are you insane?

1118
01:04:29.280 --> 01:04:31.510
Why is that so crazy?
People do that all the time.

1119
01:04:31.600 --> 01:04:35.275
They have kids, they make plans,
they get married, they buy houses.

1120
01:04:35.360 --> 01:04:37.191
That's you, Reuben. You do that.

1121
01:04:37.280 --> 01:04:39.669
That's what you do.
I don't live my life that way.

1122
01:04:39.760 --> 01:04:42.274
Is your lack of a plan
that different than my plan?

1123
01:04:42.360 --> 01:04:45.432
-I don't have a plan.
-You're on the non-plan plan.

1124
01:04:45.520 --> 01:04:48.512
-I am not on a non-plan plan.
-You are, too.

1125
01:04:48.600 --> 01:04:50.989
I've never met anybody
more afraid of commitment.

1126
01:04:51.080 --> 01:04:54.197
You were a senior delegate
at the Model UN, Polly.

1127
01:04:54.280 --> 01:04:55.952
What the hell happened to you?

1128
01:04:56.440 --> 01:04:58.431
[Leland whooping]

1129
01:05:00.320 --> 01:05:03.232
Come on, you mother!
You can do better than that!

1130
01:05:03.440 --> 01:05:05.237
I've been living my life, okay?

1131
01:05:05.320 --> 01:05:08.073
I've been in good relationships
and in shitty ones.

1132
01:05:08.160 --> 01:05:11.550
And I've moved a lot
and I've been happy and sad...

1133
01:05:11.640 --> 01:05:13.596
and lonely and that's what
I've been doing.

1134
01:05:13.680 --> 01:05:15.796
Which is more than I can say
for some freak...

1135
01:05:15.880 --> 01:05:19.077
who thinks he'll get Ebola virus
from a bowl of mixed nuts.

1136
01:05:19.200 --> 01:05:21.668
Those nuts have pee on them!
It's common sense.

1137
01:05:21.760 --> 01:05:24.797
Trust me, that is so far
beyond common sense.

1138
01:05:27.560 --> 01:05:29.312
REUBEN: You don't understand
how I grew up.

1139
01:05:29.400 --> 01:05:30.992
My mother made me
afraid of everything.

1140
01:05:31.080 --> 01:05:34.277
Big deal, Reuben.
My dad had a whole second family.

1141
01:05:34.360 --> 01:05:36.510
-What?
-Yeah, on Long lsland.

1142
01:05:36.600 --> 01:05:39.637
A wife and kids
and a golden retriever.

1143
01:05:39.840 --> 01:05:41.432
A second family?

1144
01:05:42.360 --> 01:05:44.590
Whatever. Hey, you know what?

1145
01:05:46.560 --> 01:05:48.516
I'm glad I saw that. I am.

1146
01:05:48.600 --> 01:05:52.559
Because I'm going to make this
really easy for you, Reuben.

1147
01:05:52.640 --> 01:05:55.393
I have no interest...

1148
01:05:55.520 --> 01:05:58.830
in getting married
and moving to the suburbs.

1149
01:05:58.920 --> 01:06:01.388
And obviously that's
really important to you.

1150
01:06:01.480 --> 01:06:03.835
So here's what I think
your new plan should be.

1151
01:06:03.920 --> 01:06:07.276
You should get back together
with Lisa, move into your house...

1152
01:06:07.360 --> 01:06:08.918
and move on with your life.

1153
01:06:09.000 --> 01:06:12.151
And I think you guys
will be really happy together.

1154
01:06:12.720 --> 01:06:13.869
Oh, dear Lord.

1155
01:06:15.160 --> 01:06:16.434
[Crashing]

1156
01:06:20.240 --> 01:06:22.435
REUBEN: You're not making my job
any easier.

1157
01:06:22.520 --> 01:06:25.876
Come on, Reub.
Weather report said sunny skies.

1158
01:06:29.960 --> 01:06:33.430
[Peaceful instrumental music]

1159
01:06:56.560 --> 01:06:58.357
POLLY: [On recording]
Hey, it's Polly...Prince.

1160
01:06:58.480 --> 01:07:01.790
Leave me a message,
or call back, or not.

1161
01:07:01.880 --> 01:07:03.791
You know, whatever. Okay, bye.

1162
01:07:03.880 --> 01:07:06.235
Hey, Polly, it's me. Listen...

1163
01:07:06.680 --> 01:07:10.150
I'd like to talk to you, because l
feel bad about what happened.

1164
01:07:10.960 --> 01:07:12.439
Give me a call on my cell phone.

1165
01:07:21.080 --> 01:07:22.752
[Phone rings]

1166
01:07:26.160 --> 01:07:28.310
REUBEN: Hello?
LlSA: Hi. It's Lisa.

1167
01:07:29.840 --> 01:07:30.829
Hey.

1168
01:07:30.920 --> 01:07:32.672
LlSA: So, how's the house?

1169
01:07:33.320 --> 01:07:35.231
The house is great.

1170
01:07:36.400 --> 01:07:38.311
It's big, but, you know, great.

1171
01:07:38.520 --> 01:07:41.830
LlSA: I can't wait to see it.
Did you get the gift I sent you?

1172
01:07:41.920 --> 01:07:43.558
Yeah, I did. Thanks.

1173
01:07:44.400 --> 01:07:46.118
LlSA: I really want to see you.

1174
01:07:47.400 --> 01:07:49.118
REUBEN: I don't know, Lisa.

1175
01:07:49.280 --> 01:07:50.838
Let me think about it.

